      "text": "Order No. 2023 Key Project\n\n/isoexpress/webservices/-/webservice/getSignInInfo\n\n/isoexpress/webservices/-/webservice/authenticate\n\n# Order No. 2023 Key Project\n\n### In this section\n\n- Key Projects\n- Asset Condition Reviewer Key Project\n- Capacity Auction Reforms Key Project\n- Operational Impacts of Extreme Weather Events Key Project\n- Order No. 1920 Key Project\n- Order No. 2222 Key Project\n- Order No. 2023 Key Project\n- Implemented Key Projects\n\n### Related Links\n\n- Annual Work Plan\n- Participant Readiness Project Outlook\n- Training\n- Wholesale Markets Project Plan\n\nAccess documents and resources related to Order No. 2023: Improvements to Generator Interconnection Procedures and Agreements Key Project.\n\n### Project Overview\n\nOn July 28, 2023, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) issued Order No. 2023 (RM22-14-000) mandating significant reforms to generator interconnection procedures and agreements to ensure that interconnection customers can interconnect to the transmission system in a reliable, efficient, transparent, timely, and fair manner. The reforms build on the standardized procedures that FERC established in Order Nos. 2003, 2006, and 845, and are intended to address transmission interconnection queue backlogs, improve certainty, and prevent undue discrimination for new technologies as those resources proliferate. On March 21, 2024, FERC issued Order No. 2023-A with some incremental reforms to the Order.\n\nComplying with the Order requires significant changes to the manner in which the ISO administers the transmission interconnection processes and how interconnection customers are expected to participate in those processes.\n\nPrimary elements of the Order include:\n\n- Implementing a first-ready, first-served cluster study process, eliminating New England’s current serial first-come, first-served study process\n- Speeding up interconnection queue processing through improved processes, deadlines, and penalties\n- Incorporating technological advancements into the interconnection process, including modeling and performance standards for inverter-based resources\n\n### Learning Resources\n\nBelow are important Q&A and training materials for participation in the interconnection process for the upcoming Order No. 2023 Transitional Cluster Study:\n\n- Read questions and answers on the Order Nos. 2023/2023-A transition\n- Explore Order No. 2023 and Transitional Cluster Study training resources\n- Access Knowledge Articles in Ask ISO on the 2025 Transitional Interconnection Process\n- View the ISO Public Interconnection Queue\n- Read the Interconnection Process Guide on the ISO website\n\n### Commercial Readiness Deposit (CRD) Requirements\n\nBelow are the CRD instructions and other forms required for participation in the interconnection process for the upcoming Order No. 2023 Transitional Cluster Study:\n\n- CRD Instructions, FAQs, and ISO-NE Approved Templates\n- Surety Bond Form\n- Letter of Credit (LC) Form\n- List of Approved Surety Issuers\n\nThe Order No. 2023 project is just one of several key projects at the ISO, which continuously undertakes a variety of short- and long-term projects to enhance the region’s competitive wholesale electricity markets and ensure reliable operation of the power grid.\n\n## Project-Related Documents\n\nYou can Subscribe to the event and will be notified as documents are added.\n\n### Filters\n\nKey Topic Sort by Count Sorted by Alpha\n\n| Any/All |\n| --- |\n| Asset Condition Reviewer (2) |\n| Capacity Auction Reforms (2) |\n| Day-Ahead Ancillary Services Initiative (1) |\n| Interconnection Training (5) |\n| Operational Impacts of Extreme Weather Events (2) |\n| Order No. 1920 (2) |\n| Order No. 2023 (206) |\n| Order No. 2222 (2) |\n| System Planning Training (4) |\n\nCommittee Sort by Count Sorted by Alpha\n\n| Any/All |\n| --- |\n| Markets Committee (16) |\n| Participants Committee (2) |\n| Reliability Committee (10) |\n| Transmission Committee (154) |\n\nEvent Date\n\n| NEPOOL Participants Committee Meeting - 04/09/2026 (1) |\n| --- |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 01/21/2026 (4) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 12/18/2025 (3) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 11/20/2025 (2) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 10/28/2025 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Participants Committee Meeting - 10/09/2025 (1) |\n| Transitional Cluster Study (TCS) Participation (FERC Order No. 2023) Forum - 08/28/2025 (3) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability & Transmission Committee Summer Meeting - 07/16/2025 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability & Transmission Committee Summer Meeting - 07/15/2025 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 05/22/2025 (8) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 04/17/2025 (11) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 03/26/2025 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 12/19/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 09/25/2024 (2) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability & Transmission Committee Summer Meeting - 08/14/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability & Transmission Committee Summer Meeting - 08/13/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability Committee Meeting - 07/25/2024 (5) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability Committee Meeting - 07/16/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability Committee Meeting - 06/18/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 04/25/2024 (10) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 03/27/2024 (3) |\n| FERC Order No. 2023 and ASO Studies Public Webinar - 03/26/2024 (2) |\n| NEPOOL Reliability Committee Meeting - 03/19/2024 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 02/15/2024 (34) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 02/07/2024 (5) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 02/06/2024 (5) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 01/23/2024 (21) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 01/11/2024 (3) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 01/10/2024 (3) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 01/09/2024 (3) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 01/04/2024 (5) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 12/21/2023 (14) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 12/14/2023 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 12/13/2023 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Markets Committee Meeting - 12/12/2023 (1) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 11/09/2023 (5) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 10/17/2023 (8) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 09/27/2023 (4) |\n| NEPOOL Transmission Committee Meeting - 08/22/2023 (3) |\n\nPublished Date\n\n| Any Date |\n| --- |\n\n| Start Date: | End Date: |\n| --- | --- |\n\nDocument Type Sort by Count Sorted by Alpha\n\n| Any/All |\n| --- |\n| Annual Work Plans (2) |\n| E-Learning Materials (4) |\n| FERC Filings (11) |\n| FERC Orders (4) |\n| Government Affairs Presentations (3) |\n| Meeting Materials (151) |\n| Transmission Planning Training Materials (5) |\n\nFile Type Sort by Count Sorted by Alpha\n\n| Any/All |\n| --- |\n| DOC (87) |\n| PDF (109) |\n| PPT (1) |\n| Webpage (2) |\n| ZIP (7) |\n\nFilter this list ↑\n\n### Documents\n\n| A listing of links to documents. | Title and Description | Date | Type | Size |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| ER26-1956-000 Order Accepting Revisions Related to Participation of Distributed Energy Resources in the Markets | 05/29/2026 | PDF | 188KB |\n| 2026 Annual Work Plan - Updated April 2026 | 04/09/2026 | PDF | 238KB |\n| ER26-1956-000; Revisions to Rules Related Establishment of Service for DER Participation | 03/30/2026 | PDF | 786KB |\n| 2026-01-21 TC A02 Order No. 2023 Related Changes - Section II.48.3 Redlines | 01/14/2026 | DOCX | 16KB |\n| 2026-01-21 TC A02 Order No. 2023 Related Changes - Section II.48.5 Redlines | 01/14/2026 | DOCX | 35KB |\n| 2026-01-21 TC A02 Order No. 2023 Related Changes - Section II.48.4 Redlines | 01/14/2026 | DOCX | 16KB |\n| 2026-01-21 TC A02 Order No. 2023 Related Changes - Presentation Presented by Alex Rost (ISO-NE) | 01/14/2026 | PDF | 425KB |\n| 2025-12-18 TC A03 Order No. 2023 Related Cha